channel.title: [PI] Object Help! [PI]
channel.description:
Hey guys, whenever i click on an object such as a ladder or door and i am not right next to it, it sends me a message like this: objectId: 2295 objectX: 2474 objectY: 3435
How can i get rid of this, because this will get very annoying after awhile. Thank you for your support!

item.title: [PI] Object Help! [PI]
item.dc:creator: @Whrithlin Whrithlin
item.description:
@Whrithlin wrote:

I don’t know for sure about PI, but I know it my old 317 just about everything was in the client.java, so search that for objectId. If you’re complaining about it sendMessage-ing this, then go ahead and change it, but if it’s outputting your data to the server cmd you should probably keep it, as it will come in useful later. System.out.println(“string”); is the method for that if you’re going to change it from a sendMessage.
